      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GRAYSON RED (1) did a good job to come from this draw and finish second at his most recent outing, beaten 4 metres, in a nice return to form at this circuit and distance. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw so could go one better. CAPTAIN BART (2) was runner-up from the back row last start at Menangle and came from wider than this for second three back at Penrith. Proven at this circuit and distance and a nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. GO WITHOUT (3) eases back in grade on the last attempt and had some decent form prior including a win here last month. Suited dropping to a distance where he races well and he draws nicely. ART OF TERROR (6) draws wider but did a good job in leading for a last-start win by 4 metres at this circuit and distance.",
